The paper deals with inapproximability results for fundamental problems in computer science, including the maximum independent set problem and the k-hypergraph pricing problem. These problems are studied in the areas of computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), computational geometry (cs.CG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
